(10, 14, 'K Raja Sekharan', 'kraja@gmail.com', 2147483647, 'Definitely, a common man file a case and appear himself/herself in the court to proceed with the case, but the filing should be done by following the rules and practices in force.\n\nAn advocate enrolled in Kerala in february 2015 had argued 35 cases before enrollment and won 34 of them.', 1, '2017-07-14 14:01:08', '2017-07-14 14:01:08'),
(11, 15, 'Naresh Pratap', 'naresh@gmail.com', 2147483647, 'Actually, provided that it is clear that you had no intention to defraud the restaurant, you are always legally permitted to leave a restaurant without paying.\n\nEven if it is clear that you owe the restaurant money, the restaurant has no legal right to detain you, for any period longer than it is necessary to investigate whether you have committed a fraud and to call the police to deal with it.\n\n*However*, in many places, it’s a criminal offense to not pay a restaurant, so if you leave, you might end up talking with the police later.', 1, '2017-07-14 16:24:48', '2017-07-14 16:24:48'),
(6, 8, 'fenil patel', 'fpatel@gmail.com', 2147483647, 'No, a woman is considered innocent even if proven guilty.\n\nRemember the case of “Braveheart Sisters” from Rohtak?\n\nThe video of two sisters trashing men had gone viral, and the media was quick to call the girls braveheart sisters without verifying the facts. The accused men were humiliated throughout the country. One of them was about to become a solider in the Indian Army, but his career was damaged for ever.\n\nAnd if not for the investigation by a freelance journalist and men’s rights activist, the truth would have been buried for ever. The investigation revealed the women had a history of blackmailing men. In fact, on the day of the incident, according to several eye witnesses, the women had an alteration over a seat in a bus, and used the women privilege to claim that they had been molested.\n\nBut the sad part is that even after the investigation, the media that tarnished the image of the accused did not apologize. Indian feminists continue to demand sexist laws. Apparently, women are always the victims even if proven otherwise!\n\nJustice, RIP\n\nA Supreme Court ruling suggests that an Indian women would never lie about rape, so a rape accusation can be taken as truth unless otherwise proven.\n\nDoes anyone seriously think that it is not possible for women to lie about rape because of social “stigma”? Heck, far from social stigma, rape stories go viral, which some unscrupulous women have exploited to form organized gangs to blackmail gullible men of rape and extort money.\n\nRape may be a crime, but biased laws are a violation of constitutional right to equality.\n\nBlackstone''s formulation is the principle that: "It is better that ten guilty persons escape than that one innocent suffer”.\n\nThis is a principle that applies in democracies around the world, from petty thieves to terrorists like Ajmal Kasab, except Indian men accused of rape.', 1, '2017-07-14 12:07:43', '2017-07-14 12:07:43'),
(7, 8, 'Mauli Pandey', 'mpandey@yahoo.com', 1596549872, 'First off, ‘always’ never works. Contexts differ, situations differ, victims and perpetrators differ. Never use ‘always’.\n\nI am assuming that this question is situated in the specific context of “sexual assault crimes”. Yes, in such crimes, the accused is presumed guilty until proven innocent. Many countries, including India, have such legality around the matter.\n\nHaving said that, for most crimes involving accused from both genders, matters proceed without either genders being presumed innocent. Both parties are treated equally before the eyes of law.\n\nNow, to the real reason!\n\nSome women are fucking assholes! There is no better way of saying this. They press false charges. They set back the fight for justice for their female counterparts and men who are sexually assaulted (men’s rape isn’t legally recognized yet in India). They trivialize rape for their personal motives, making a mockery of real survivors.\n\nHaving said that, this false reportage happens primarily in cities. Highly unlikely this happens in rural India. I am inclined to believe that even if a woman reports assault in a far flung village, she will be questioned and not her perpetrators. In all likelihood, the complaint won’t even make it to charge sheet.\n\nMy only request is to deter people from making statements such as these - “In India, a woman is always innocent until proven guilty, and a man is always guilty until proven innocent." Because it makes a sweeping generalization! Indian women seem like unfair and morally ambiguous human beings, while painting a picture that Indian men have it so hard.\n\nAnd that is where the problem is! It is a grey area, but we have to talk about it without falling prey to generalizations and without being charged with emotions.', 1, '2017-07-14 12:09:10', '2017-07-14 12:09:10'),
(8, 9, 'neel patel', 'neel456@gmail.com', 2147483647, 'Meet the doctor that could predict 10/10 the sex of a child just by looking at the pregnant mother!\n\nBefore 1989, in a communist Romania, we didn’t have ecography for pregnant women. So they didn’t know the sex of the child before birth.\n\nYet, in one of Bucharest (capital city of Romania)’s hospitals, one doctor had a 100% succesful rate of “anticipating” the sex of the child by looking at the pregnant mother’s womb, in exchange for a certain amount of money.\n\nHe would write the sex of the baby in a notebook, along with the date and the mother’s name. But… He would write the opposite of what he would tell the mother, without anybody checking. For instance, he would say “You’ll have a boy!”. And would write in the book “Girl. 9th of July 1985. Elena Popescu”.\n\nIf Elena had a boy, she would admit that the doctor really had some strange powers. If she had a girl and went to confront the doctor, he would just pull out the notebook and tell “I never told you are going to have a boy, I even wrote here it is going to be a girl”.', 1, '2017-07-14 12:10:00', '2017-07-14 12:10:00'),
(9, 10, 'rahul gandhi', 'ragapogo@ymail.com', 2147483647, 'Well, I can tell you that in Italy, when a small restaurant owner tells you “Oh, so sorry, our credit card system is broken…” you should just say, “Gosh, I don’t have any cash - thanks for the free meal.”\n\nWhen he/she argues and threatens, you simply say: “Well, call the police.” Instantly, his credit card system will work again.\n\nWhy the sudden capitulation? In Italy, tax avoidance is so rampant that small business owners try to deal in cash as much as possible.\n\nLaws in Italy allow police to stop customers coming out of businesses and ask to see credit card receipts. (a whole system of regulations…etc, to ensure records of business activity exists)\n\nThe owner knows this and will yield.', 1, '2017-07-14 12:10:44', '2017-07-14 12:10:44'),
(12, 16, 'Vraj Mavani', 'vmanani@yahoo.com', 2147483647, 'Many governments operate on the Silver Platter doctrine. As long as they did not commit the crime to get the information they are free to use the information. Think of the bank records stolen from Swiss banks used in tax cases, the records taken from the Bahamas, BVI and Panama being used for corruption and tax investigations. So if a hacker found evidence of corruption and they wished to give it to the government, there is not problem. They might even earn a reward.', 1, '2017-07-14 16:28:09', '2017-07-14 16:28:09'),
(13, 12, 'Robert Christian', 'robertc@gmail.com', 2147483647, 'Brokers are not customarily used for US apartment rentals except in NYC. Someone must be available to show it to prospective tenants. Your current tenant might be willing to do it for a fee. You can list it online yourself.', 1, '2017-07-14 16:32:04', '2017-07-14 16:32:04'),
(14, 12, 'Anita Patel', 'anitha@gmail.com', 2147483647, 'Riding a bicycle in the public roadway, with the flow of traffic, is legal, and correct, in California, and in most of the U.S., with the exception of certain freeways, etc. It is legal whether or not there is a marked bike lane.', 1, '2017-07-14 16:33:21', '2017-07-14 16:33:21'),
(15, 11, 'Anita Patel', 'anitha@gmail.com', 2147483647, 'Riding a bicycle in the public roadway, with the flow of traffic, is legal, and correct, in California, and in most of the U.S., with the exception of certain freeways, etc. It is legal whether or not there is a marked bike lane.', 1, '2017-07-14 16:34:06', '2017-07-14 16:34:06'),
(16, 11, 'Raj Prajapati', 'raj@hotmail.com', 2147483647, 'It is also legal for a bicyclist to ride in the lane of motor vehicle traffic and use the full lane. Generally the law stipulates that a bicyclist should ride as far to the right as is "practicable," but it''s still permissible for bikes to use the lane of traffic if there are good reasons to do so. Here are some common reasons that bicyclists may use the full lane or ride further to the left: ', 1, '2017-07-14 16:35:19', '2017-07-14 16:35:19'),
(17, 17, 'Julia Martin', 'julia@gmail.com', 2147483647, 'I did. Big mistake. We were married for 8 years, divorced for 2 and remarried on our 10 yr anniversary. I remarried him for the 2nd time because he tried hard to win me back. He swore off alcohol, he got responsible with money, he started being a dad to the kids and wanting to do things with us again. I thought the 2nd time around would be better, and it would be better for our kids to get back together. For the first 3 years it was great. Then it all went back to the way it was. Now I''m in divorce round 2.', 1, '2017-07-14 16:38:23', '2017-07-14 16:38:23'),
(18, 19, 'Madhav Parikh', 'madhavp@gmail.com', 2147483647, 'You need to file for copyright protection for it as a ‘literary work’. It’s a fairly easy and reasonable process.\n\nCheck out the portal www.trademarkclick.com where you can do this easily by simply filing in a small form.', 1, '2017-07-14 16:41:44', '2017-07-14 16:41:44'),
(19, 20, 'Kevin Shah', 'kshah@gmail.com', 778956231, 'I do not believe that, without more, that money transfer would be criminal. However, if a money judgment is entered against you and you claim you have no money, your creditor has a right to discover your assets which is done by your being deposed under oath. Your creditor will eventually discover that you moved money to another country and when you did it. She/he will argue in court that that was a fraudulent transfer (i.e., a transfer to hide assets). Accordingly, move your money BEFORE you are served with a lawsuit.', 1, '2017-07-14 16:44:10', '2017-07-14 16:44:10'),
(20, 21, 'Mumukshu shah', 'mumushi@gmail.com', 2147483647, 'It is illegal to charge you over the MRP, be it any vendor.\n\nBut because of the implementation of GST, there has been quite a confusion.\n\nIf the MRP of the product is Rs.100 and because of the GST, it increased to Rs.108. The vendors can print the new MRP in stickers and stick them to the packet and charge the consumer more than the previous MRP. This is quite understandable.\n\nHowever this is allowed only for three months from July 2017 to September 2017. After this period, the vendors are expected to clear off the old stock and come up with new MRPs that include the GST as well, that are printed directly on the packages. Using stickers to hide the existing MRPs or the expiry dates with new ones is illegal too(except for this 3 month grace period).', 1, '2017-07-14 16:46:31', '2017-07-14 16:46:31'),
(21, 22, 'Ali Khan', 'alikhan@gmail.com', 2147483647, 'There are individual Muslims or even small Islamic groups who out of fear of the negative effect Islamic terrorism has had on the view of Islam by westerners (frequenting almost weekly our TV screens), are keen to express their personal abhorrence of these atrocities. This unfortunately is a rare phenomenon and too little and perhaps too late.\n\nIn the UK whenever there is a Islamic terrorist incident the Muslim community is for the most part silent. That is contrary to the impression from the comments to this Quora question that Muslims en masse are condemning the violence done in the name of Islam.', 1, '2017-07-14 16:49:46', '2017-07-14 16:49:46'),
(22, 23, 'Motilal Ghandhi', 'motilal@gmail.com', 2147483647, 'Employment law generally deals with individual employment contracts in which the employee is not either a member of a union or bound by a collective bargaining agreement.\n\nLabour law generally applies to work environments that are governed by the Ontario Labour Relations Act. In such environments, the employee is subject to collective bargaining and is a member of a union.\n\nOne main distinction is that whereas employment contracts can be either oral or written, collective bargaining agreements cannot be oral. While both employment and labour law involve similar issues, the laws, cases and procedures for both are different.', 1, '2017-07-14 16:52:09', '2017-07-14 16:52:09'),
(23, 24, 'Puran Choudhari', 'puran@gmail.com', 2147483647, 'Since she’s your wife, anything you leave to her at your death is inherited tax-free and furthermore, life insurance proceeds are not taxed as income to the recipient anyway.\n\nAnother answer mentioned a $5 million exclusion from the estate tax. While there is an exclusion on assets passed to other people at death, it is irrelevant when you are passing assets to a spouse, since 100% of assets passed to a spouse are exempt from any kind of tax.', 1, '2017-07-14 16:54:27', '2017-07-14 16:54:27'),
(24, 25, 'Mukul Sharma', 'mukul@gmail.com', 2147483647, 'The standard expiration date for most checks is 180 days (six months) and personal checks are included in this policy. In the United States, banks are privately owned and not government operated so banks do have the right to refuse your deposit if there happens to be any suspicion of the item''s negotiability.\n\nIf a check happens to have conditional verbiage on it, such as "void after 90 days" this also would fall under the bank''s discretion.\n\nChecks that are accepted after 180 days are subject to being returned by the issuing bank. A noteworthy exception to this rule would be any government checks, or certified funds (such as a cashier''s check) which are typically honored for extended amounts of time.', 1, '2017-07-14 16:56:44', '2017-07-14 16:56:44'),
(25, 26, 'Ram Jethmalani', 'ram@gmail.com', 2147483647, 'If the child has not completed five years of age, then the mother is the lawful guardian, without doubt! But if the child has completed or is above 5 years old then the father is the lawful guardian.\n\nBut in this case, as the father is not present here to take care of the child as he is in prison and welfare of the child is the utmost consideration then the mother will get full custody of the child.', 1, '2017-07-14 16:58:57', '2017-07-14 16:58:57'),
(26, 27, 'Kajal Chodhari', 'kajal@gmail.com', 2147483647, 'Yes, Roshan there is act for that in our constitutition against these illegal adminstration. ', 1, '2017-07-14 17:03:00', '2017-07-14 17:03:00'),
(27, 28, 'John Firgh', 'john@gmail.com', 2147483647, 'By providing a benefit to the workers beyond attempting to price-fix wages and monopolize labor and/or by providing a benefit to the employers beyond not-walking-out or not-suing.', 1, '2017-07-14 17:05:14', '2017-07-14 17:05:14'),
(28, 29, 'Rajat Sharma', 'rajat@gmail.com', 2147483647, 'Interesting things to consider, albeit quite fictional. Check out the FAR / AIM documents that the FAA publishes. You will find a whole lot of information there that will help bring some level of believability to your fiction story. Above a certain altitude, your superhero will need a tank of O2 and a mask system to breathe it. Above a certain airspeed Mr. superhero will need to protect his skin and eyes. And when he gets to extreme temperatures with altitude he will need to have a nice wooly jacket and gloves. \n', 1, '2017-07-14 17:08:07', '2017-07-14 17:08:07'),
(29, 30, 'Balbir Singh', 'balbir@gmail.com', 2147483647, 'Supposedly their newly passed law, though it is highly questionable why a committee under the executive branch could do something that always requires court orders. perhaps they’re using emergency order but that’s usually not what this is for.\n\nBut hey, the goal here is never to follow the law.', 1, '2017-07-14 17:10:09', '2017-07-14 17:10:09'),
(30, 31, 'Yogesh Martin', 'yogila@gmail.com', 2147483647, 'They don’t necessarily know that that will provide a comprehensive analysis, that is just the amount of time they have authorized for the assesment. Obviously, such a report would be of little value if the researchers were allowed an indefinite period to provide a result. The goal is to collect as much data as possible, like all research there will undoubtedly be areas that may warrant further inquiry. The Commission can allocate additional time and funds to answering those questions if they feel the need.', 1, '2017-07-14 17:12:41', '2017-07-14 17:12:41');
